===Etymology===
Coined by [[:w:Harold Urey|Harold Urey]], an American chemist, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|lang=grc|δεύτερος}} ‘second’ + [[-ium]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/djuːˈtɪɹiəm/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/dju:"tIri@m/}}
* {{hyphenation|deu|te|ri|um}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{isotope}} An [[isotope]] of [[hydrogen]] formed of one [[proton]] and one [[neutron]] in each atom - {{nuclide|2|1|H}}.
#: ''Heavy water is “heavy” because it contains '''deuterium'''.''
# An atom of this isotope.
#: ''There were about 80 '''deuteriums''' for every million protiums, and virtually no tritium.''

